<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06168168 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06168168 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: From pop acts at the Great America amusement park to classiccharm at the classy Carmel Bach Festival, the Bay Area and central coast arealive with music this summer. But steering clear of the crush for seats takessome skill.  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  ENTERTAINMENT; SHOW; SALE; GUIDELINE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  EACH of the special summer attractions in the South Bay and outlying areas hasits own way of marketing tickets. Get to know the landscape, and you'll have abetter chance at the concerts, seats and prices you want.;    (check) PaulMasson Summer Series: This year the Paul Masson series is selling its ticketsthrough BASS. However if you buy your tickets in person from the BASS outletat 29 N. San Pedro St., San Jose, there's no service charge. The box office isopen 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. Monday through Friday.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Arts andamp; Books  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  A FESTIVAL OF MUSICAL CHAIRS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Cover StorySee related stories pages 3, 12, and 13 of this section.  </MEMO><TEXT>     If you already have some Paul Masson tickets and can get into the venue,the Paul Masson box office is open for walk-up sales during performances andthere's no service charge.;    Paul Masson sells many of its tickets by mailorder before the season begins. To get on the mailing list for next year'sperformances, send a post card with your name and address to P.O. Box 1852,Saratoga, 95070.;    For recorded ticket information, call (408) 741-5181.;   (check) Villa Montalvo: Villa Montalvo charges $3 per order for handling phoneor mail orders. There's no charge if you buy tickets at the box office, 15400Montalvo Road, Saratoga. The box office is open 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Mondaythrough Saturday and 1 p.m. to 4 p.m. Sundays. It's also open before someperformances.;    Tickets for shows that have not sold out are available atthe door, and if shows do sell out early, Villa Montalvo sometimes sets up twosets of bleachers on either side of the stage that are discounted about 25percent. The bleacher seats usually go on sale about a week before the show.;   Finally, members of the non-profit Villa Montalvo get a 10 percent discounton tickets. Call the box office, (408) 741-3428, for more information.;   (check) Great America: The Santa Clara amusement park sells tickets duringoperating hours for its concerts at the park.;    To get into a concert, youhave to buy an admission ticket. Great America has promotional deals with Mandamp;MMars candy through July 31 (bring a Mars candy wrapper and get $4 off) andwith Longs Drugs Aug. 1 through Sept. 2 (pick up a voucher at the drug storesgood for $3 off).;    The park also has group sales plans. Call (408) 988-1800for recorded information.;    (check) Cabrillo Music Festival: There's noservice charge for festival tickets bought at the door of the Santa Cruz CivicAuditorium. The service charge for advance tickets bought at the auditorium'sbox office or by phone is $1 per ticket. The box office, on the corner ofCenter and Church streets, is open 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday through Friday and10 a.m. to 2 p.m. Saturday and Sunday.;    Subscription holders save 10percent on single-ticket prices. Students and seniors get discounts, too. Callthe box office at (408) 429-3444.;    (check) Shoreline Amphitheatre:Shoreline Amphitheatre has its own box office directly under the marquee atthe Mountain View concert venue. There's no service charge if you buy ticketsat the box office in person. Hours are 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday through Fridayand on some weekends when major shows go on sale. The box office does notaccept checks, nor does it take phone orders. Call (415) 967-4040 for recordedinformation.;    For some big shows, the box office opens a day ahead of timeoffering limited tickets for Mountain View residents. You must have aShoreline ID card, available at the box office from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m.weekdays, and another form of ID with your Mountain View address. For recordedinformation on upcoming shows and pre-sale tickets, call (415) 968-6862.;   (check) Carmel Bach Festival: You can buy tickets in person at the festival'soffice in Room 11, Sunset Center (corner of San Carlos and Ninth streets),Carmel.;    But since not all of us can be in Carmel, the festival charges $2per order to take phone or fax orders. Call (408) 624-1521 for generalinformation, (408) 624-2788 to fax.;    (check) Shakespeare Santa Cruz:Starting Monday, you can buy your tickets at the University of California,Santa Cruz, Performing Arts Center box office and pay no service charge. Hoursare 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday through Friday. The box office will be openduring weekend and evening shows starting July 20.;    There's a $2 per ordercharge to get tickets by phone. Call (408) 459-4168 for information.;   Shakespeare Santa Cruz has four subscription plans that save up to 21 percentoff single ticket prices. The group also offers student, senior and groupdiscounts.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Kathleen Donnelly  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910616  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  12  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  835  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday June 16, 199100168168,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>